=========== FUNCTION SUMMARY ========
    Main functions:
	  Measure temperature and humidity
      Measure air quality
      Display date and time
      Alert when temperature or air quality exceeds the threshold
    Additional functions:
      Alarm clock
      Adjustable temperature and air quality thresholds
      Adjustable date and time
      Auto turn-off LED after 10 seconds of inactivity (no alert or sound)
      Navigate and adjust values using buttons

============ USER GUIDE ============
    There are 4 buttons from left to right:
    Button 1:  Move the cursor to the left   
    Button 2:  Move the cursor to the right
    Button 3:   + Short press: Increase the selected value by 1 unit
                + Hold:        Decrease the selected value
  
    Button 4:   + Hold for 1 second: Turn ON/OFF the alarm (shown on LCD)
                + Short press:   .Stop the alarm (buzzer)
                                 .Turn off buzzer and LEDs during over-threshold alert
                                 .Exit edit mode when cursor is active
                                 .Temporarily mute all alerts

============== Other Notes =============
    +The LED will automatically turn off after 10s if there is no sound, temperature, air, or alarm alert
    +When the LED is off, it can be reactivated by making a sound or pressing the left/right button
    +When the cursor is on temperature or gas values, it will display the threshold value for easy adjustment


